C utility library
─────────────────
This is less a proper “library” and more a grab bag of useful things I find
myself repeatedly implementing. Symbols are not namespace-prefixed in the way a
library would usually be structured, so you probably want to copy anything you
want into your own project and rename the symbols.

Only Clang/GCC on Linux are supported. Compatibility with other environments is
best effort.

Everything in this library is in the public domain. Use it any way you wish.
